140
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:54,750
of the immense privilege
I was afforded in my childhood.

141
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:56,625
[STUDENTS] You commoners
are even more amazing

142
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:58,125
than I thought!

143
00:06:58,208 --> 00:06:59,166
[KIMITO]
Uh...

144
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,375
I am ready to proceed.

145
00:07:01,458 --> 00:07:04,416
Even if I must wait several
hours, I shall endure it.

146
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:05,458
Same here!

147
00:07:05,541 --> 00:07:07,416
I will wait as long
as is required!

148
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,000
[KUJO]
Ladies.

149
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:11,375
I appreciate your patience, but
the wait won't be long at all.

150
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:14,583
This restaurant serves what
Commoner's call "fast food."

151
00:07:14,666 --> 00:07:17,125
Expediency is the general idea.

152
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:18,791
Your meal will be
ready for consumption

153
00:07:18,875 --> 00:07:20,958
within one minute of
your order's placement.

154
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:26,166
[STUDENTS]
Oh! My word!

155
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:27,625
[STUDENTS]
My word!

156
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:29,083
[KIMITO]
They said that twice.

157
00:07:29,166 --> 00:07:30,125
[STUDENT 6D]
I don't understand.

158
00:07:30,208 --> 00:07:31,666
How do they prepare
it so quickly?

159
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:33,916
[STUDENT 6E]
It defies logic. It's insane.

160
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:34,833
[STUDENT 6F]
These Commoners.

161
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:36,541
Who are they, exactly?

162
00:07:36,625 --> 00:07:37,458
[STUDENT 6G]
Well, they're...

163
00:07:37,541 --> 00:07:38,833
