247
00:10:53,208 --> 00:10:55,416
the moment my teeth
pierce the bun.

248
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:56,583
A bun baked with wheat

249
00:10:56,666 --> 00:10:59,458
straight from the
fields of Elysium!

250
00:10:59,541 --> 00:11:02,250
If ever I thought I loved
burgers before this moment,

251
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:04,583
then I was a fool.

252
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:06,375
No--A prisoner.

253
00:11:06,458 --> 00:11:08,958
Chained in Plato's cave,
feeding on shadows,

254
00:11:09,041 --> 00:11:11,666
woefully ignorant of
the true form of meat!

255
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:13,125
But I'm ascending now.

256
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:14,375
I taste veggies.

257
00:11:14,458 --> 00:11:16,666
Lettuce crisper than a
bank of sunkissed snow.

258
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:19,750
The sharp, sweet tang
of artisanal pickles.

259
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:23,750
The savory damp of blood-red
tomato sinking into beef.

260
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:27,333
All hail the triumvirate
of veggie, bun and flesh!

261
00:11:27,416 --> 00:11:30,416
All in proportion!
All in harmony!

262
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:32,041
You were wrong, Pythagoras.

263
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:34,750
You should've eaten meat!
Muscles are delicious!

264
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:37,083
In my mouth, I mean--No, damnit!

265
00:11:37,166 --> 00:11:39,666
No, this isn't right!

266
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:44,166
[STUDENT 6K]
Umm, are you okay?

267
00:11:44,250 --> 00:11:45,666
[STUDENT 6L]
Is something the matter?

268
00:11:45,750 --> 00:11:48,375
[KIMITO] This burger is too good
and I won't stand for it!

269
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:49,791
If they think I'm gonna sit here

270
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:52,500
and let them sell a perfectly
crafted burger like this

271
00:11:52,583 --> 00:11:55,041
at a fast food restaurant,
they're wrong!

272
00:11:55,125 --> 00:11:57,333
Fast food burgers are
supposed to taste like crap!

273
00:11:57,416 --> 00:11:58,833
That's a general rule of thumb!

274
00:11:58,916 --> 00:12:01,208
And not only that, they're
supposed to be dirt-cheap!

275
00:12:01,291 --> 00:12:03,458
You could charge
millions for this!

276
00:12:03,541 --> 00:12:04,708
[KIMITO growls]

277
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:06,458
I won't let you make
a mockery of fast food!

278
00:12:06,541 --> 00:12:07,916
So whoever made this--

279
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:10,625
Meet me outside.

280
00:12:12,041 --> 00:12:14,416
[STUDENT 6M] Oh dear,
Kimito seems really upset.

281
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,875
I don't understand why,

282
00:12:15,958 --> 00:12:18,875
but you're right,
he appears extremely enraged.

283
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,000
[SAKIMORI]
Hakua!

284
00:12:32,208 --> 00:12:33,208
[SAKIMORI]
What are you doing?

285
00:12:33,291 --> 00:12:35,500
Are you going to visit Kimito?

286
00:12:35,583 --> 00:12:37,000
Oh, dear. He's out.

287
00:12:37,083 --> 00:12:39,791
Kimito and the other students
took a trip to Shominland,

288
00:12:39,875 --> 00:12:42,041
Seikain's new
Commoner theme park.

289
00:13:01,583 --> 00:13:02,958
Kimito...

290
00:13:03,041 --> 00:13:05,208
I just want to say how happy
I am that you're with us.

291
00:13:05,291 --> 00:13:07,583
And on such a
monumental occasion!

292
00:13:07,666 --> 00:13:08,958
I'm glad to be here.

293
00:13:09,041 --> 00:13:10,458
Oh!

294
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:12,541
It appears they have many
plushies just over there, Reiko.

295
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,666
Shall we go play?

296
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:15,750
Sure!

297
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,416
I'll go with you, as well!

298
00:13:19,166 --> 00:13:22,125
[game noises]

299
00:13:24,708 --> 00:13:26,125
I did it, everyone!

300
00:13:31,791 --> 00:13:33,166
[KIMITO]
Yup. That's Reiko.

301
00:13:33,708 --> 00:13:38,041
[game music playing]

302
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:40,083
[KIMITO] Aika's really good
at the dancing game.

303
00:13:40,166 --> 00:13:42,375
I was hoping she
would get to show it.

304
00:13:42,458 --> 00:13:44,916
But most of these girls are
stuck at the claw machine.

305
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,750
Those plushies
are just too cute.

306
00:13:50,875 --> 00:13:52,500
[KAREN grunting]

307
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,250
[KIMITO] They'll probably
come over here in a while.

308
00:13:57,333 --> 00:13:58,583
We just have to be patient.

309
00:14:03,041 --> 00:14:04,583
[TWIN 6A]
Excuse me!

310
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:05,750
Sorry to interrupt,

311
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:06,833
but if you're not busy,

312
00:14:06,916 --> 00:14:08,125
would you mind showing
my sister and me

313
00:14:08,208 --> 00:14:09,708
how to play the plushy game?

314
00:14:09,791 --> 00:14:11,708
We're clueless,
we could use some help!

315
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:13,833
[KIMITO]
Well, uh...

316
00:14:13,916 --> 00:14:15,583
[AIKA] Don't worry
about me, I'll be fine.

317
00:14:15,666 --> 00:14:16,625
Are you sure?

318
00:14:16,708 --> 00:14:18,000
I'm gonna go
buy somethin' to drink.

319
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:27,166
[KIMITO] I'm aiming for this one
right here, so watch close.

320
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:42,791
[KIMITO]
Here you go.

321
00:14:42,875 --> 00:14:44,166
You would give this to me?

322
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:46,041
[KIMITO]
Of course.

323
00:14:46,125 --> 00:14:47,416
Thanks so much, Kimito!

324
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:49,750
I will treasure this
for the rest of my life!

325
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:51,083
[TWINS laugh]

326
00:14:51,166 --> 00:14:53,583
Hey. Do you wanna try it too?

327
00:14:53,666 --> 00:14:54,416
I do.

328
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,333
Well... Here goes.

329
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:57,750
I hope it works.

330
00:15:01,041 --> 00:15:01,750
[KIMITO]
That's perfect.

331
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:02,750
Now let go of the button!

332
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:03,958
Ooh... ah, ah!

333
00:15:04,041 --> 00:15:05,541
Wh-What do I do now?

334
00:15:05,625 --> 00:15:06,708
You're okay.

335
00:15:06,791 --> 00:15:08,416
If I were you,
I'd aim for that blue one.

336
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:09,875
I think you can snag it.

337
00:15:11,791 --> 00:15:12,625
[STUDENT 4I]
Oh...

338
00:15:12,708 --> 00:15:14,458
[KIMITO]
Good luck.

339
00:15:14,541 --> 00:15:16,625
[STUDENT 4I]
Right. Thanks!

340
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:18,500
Oh, Kimito!

341
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:21,000
[KIMITO]
Oh, yeah. That's it.

342
00:15:21,083 --> 00:15:24,083
Almost there, just
a little bit deeper.

343
00:15:24,166 --> 00:15:27,958
[STUDENT 4I]
Oh... oh!

344
00:15:28,041 --> 00:15:29,125
[KIMITO]
How's that?

345
00:15:29,208 --> 00:15:32,166
[STUDENT 4I]
Great! No, perfect.

346
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:34,250
Big and so strong.

347
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:37,375
What a wonderful feeling.

348
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:38,916
Here comes your prize.

349
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,833
No! Not yet!

350
00:15:40,916 --> 00:15:42,666
Sorry, but I have to pull out.

351
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:45,541
No, please! I want more!

352
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,333
So much more!

353
00:15:47,416 --> 00:15:49,208
[screaming]

354
00:15:53,541 --> 00:15:54,791
[KIMITO]
Look! You got it!

355
00:15:54,875 --> 00:15:56,750
[STUDENT 4I]
I enjoyed that very much.

356
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:58,875
Whelp, I'd better take off...

357
00:15:58,958 --> 00:15:59,625
[gasps]

358
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:01,000
[STUDENT 6O]
Kimito!

359
00:16:01,083 --> 00:16:02,833
Would you show me how
to do that, as well, please?

360
00:16:02,916 --> 00:16:06,875
[overlapping chatter]

361
00:16:06,958 --> 00:16:08,250
What do you say?

362
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:10,166
Please instruct us!
We'll be forever in your debt.

363
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:12,458
You got one
earlier easily enough.

364
00:16:18,208 --> 00:16:19,166
[KIMITO]
That's weird.

365
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:21,000
Where did Aika run off to?

366
00:16:21,083 --> 00:16:21,833
What is this?

367
00:16:21,916 --> 00:16:25,125
Is it some kind of stage?

368
00:16:25,208 --> 00:16:28,625
Oh. It's just a game
where you dance to music.

369
00:16:28,708 --> 00:16:29,416
Want me to show you?

370
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,791
[STUDENTS]
Yes, please!

371
00:16:33,458 --> 00:16:39,750
[game music plays]

372
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:41,666
[KIMITO]
See? Like this.

373
00:16:46,916 --> 00:16:48,375
[STUDENTS]
Ooh!

374
00:16:48,458 --> 00:16:50,583
[KIMITO]
It's pretty fun.

375
00:16:50,666 --> 00:16:53,333
Well, do any of you
wanna give it a try?

376
00:16:53,416 --> 00:16:54,708
[STUDENT 6R]
Yes!

377
00:16:54,791 --> 00:16:56,083
Oh...

378
00:16:56,166 --> 00:16:57,333
I wouldn't take off my shoes,
that's kinda gross.

379
00:17:02,083 --> 00:17:03,208
Look, I think I won!

380
00:17:03,291 --> 00:17:04,708
You were wonderful!

381
00:17:04,791 --> 00:17:05,666
Slow down.

382
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:06,958
You have to beat 'em all to win!

383
00:17:07,041 --> 00:17:08,625
[STUDENTS]
You can't be serious?

384
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:16,958
[STUDENTS]
I am so sorry about that!

385
00:17:17,041 --> 00:17:18,833
This game is far too hard.

386
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:22,541
Perhaps it's best we give up.

387
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:24,416
Commoner pastimes
could be too difficult

388
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,916
for us to achieve success.

389
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,125
[AIKA]
Are you kidding?

390
00:17:27,208 --> 00:17:28,291
Just watch me!

391
00:17:29,458 --> 00:17:31,875
See? Concentrate. It's easy!

392
00:17:31,958 --> 00:17:33,916
[music continues]

393
00:17:36,125 --> 00:17:37,375
[AIKA]
Ready? Go!

394
00:17:37,458 --> 00:17:39,083
Up! Down! Up! Down!

395
00:17:39,166 --> 00:17:41,208
Keep both feet
together as best you can!

396
00:17:41,291 --> 00:17:43,750
The next part is hard,
so stay loose, kay?

397
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:45,875
[STUDENT 6R]
Uh... Right!

398
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,083
[AIKA]
And jump!

399
00:17:50,875 --> 00:17:52,375
[AIKA]
We're almost to the end!

400
00:17:52,458 --> 00:17:54,333
Just keep your
movements nice and tight!

401
00:17:54,416 --> 00:17:56,000
All right,
I'll do my best!

402
00:18:01,666 --> 00:18:03,958
--[AIKA] Yeah!
--[STUDENTS cheering]

403
00:18:08,208 --> 00:18:09,708
[AIKA]
We rocked!

404
00:18:15,083 --> 00:18:17,583
I mean... Good job.

405
00:18:19,208 --> 00:18:20,541
Thank you very much, Aika.

406
00:18:20,625 --> 00:18:21,791
I'm impressed.

407
00:18:21,875 --> 00:18:24,541
I had no idea you were
an expert at this game!

408
00:18:28,625 --> 00:18:31,166
Well... Guess I am!

409
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:32,541
Aika!

410
00:18:32,625 --> 00:18:34,583
I really hope you'll teach me
how to play it, too!

411
00:18:34,666 --> 00:18:36,458
[STUDENT 6E]
Oh yes! Same here! Teach me!

412
00:18:36,541 --> 00:18:39,041
[overlapping chatter]

413
00:18:42,208 --> 00:18:44,708
Sure. I'd be glad to!

414
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:46,750
[STUDENTS chattering]

415
00:18:47,208 --> 00:18:50,041
[AIKA] The most important thing
you need is a sense of rhythm.

416
00:18:50,125 --> 00:18:51,625
[KIMITO]
You really did it.

417
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:55,000
[AIKA] You just have to practice
your moves and do your best!

418
00:18:56,375 --> 00:18:59,333
[KAREN cooing, laughing]

419
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:07,833
[AIKA] I'd like to order an
extra grande hazelnut vanilla

420
00:19:07,916 --> 00:19:09,833
almond Foamuccino,
heavy on the caramel,

421
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:11,458
heavy on the whipped
cocoa rhumba cream

422
00:19:11,541 --> 00:19:13,833
with an extra shot
to top it off, please!

423
00:19:13,916 --> 00:19:16,583
Wow! What an incredibly
artful order, Aika!

424
00:19:16,666 --> 00:19:18,416
Seeing her imbued
with such confidence

425
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:20,666
in a drink order
is quite reassuring.

426
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:23,541
[AIKA laughs]
I do what I can!

427
00:19:23,625 --> 00:19:24,833
Tell me this much, Aika.

428
00:19:24,916 --> 00:19:26,125
When Commoners order a coffee,

429
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:28,041
do they all speak such
a complicated, strange,

430
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:29,291
and confusing language?

431
00:19:29,375 --> 00:19:30,708
It is quite overwhelming.

432
00:19:30,791 --> 00:19:33,000
Do you think we'll be able
to master this technique?

433
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:34,500
I wouldn't worry about it!

434
00:19:34,583 --> 00:19:36,916
That was totally an
advanced-level order.

435
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:40,083
Just start off by asking for
a latte, iced or hot is fine.

436
00:19:40,166 --> 00:19:43,083
Well, Reiko, is anything
on the menu catching your eye?

437
00:19:43,166 --> 00:19:45,666
[STUDENT 6V] I am very curious
about these Foamuccinos.

438
00:19:45,750 --> 00:19:47,291
[STUDENT 6Q]
What exactly is a Foamuccino?

439
00:19:47,375 --> 00:19:48,500
[KAE]
Is everything all right?

440
00:19:48,583 --> 00:19:50,541
[STUDENT 4A]
Yes, Aika, do tell us, please.

441
00:19:51,541 --> 00:19:53,500
[STUDENTS chattering]

442
00:19:59,791 --> 00:20:02,041
[STUDENT 4H] What is this
little hole in the top for?

443
00:20:02,125 --> 00:20:03,291
Oh. Yes.

444
00:20:03,375 --> 00:20:05,208
You must enlighten us,
what does the hole do?

445
00:20:05,291 --> 00:20:07,625
Uh... Well...

446
00:20:07,708 --> 00:20:08,833
I think I know.

447
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:10,791
Is the hole from
where one drinks?

448
00:20:11,791 --> 00:20:13,708
That's right! Here, watch me.

449
00:20:13,791 --> 00:20:15,791
I'll show you how
the Commoners do it.

450
00:20:16,916 --> 00:20:19,166
[AIKA screaming]

451
00:20:20,708 --> 00:20:23,250
[AIKA whimpering]

452
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:24,250
Are you all right?

453
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:26,041
Do we need
to fetch a physician?

454
00:20:26,125 --> 00:20:28,000
Perhaps this will
help you cool down!

455
00:20:30,708 --> 00:20:32,166
[AIKA]
Sorry about that!

456
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:35,208
These are real hot.
Slipped my mind.

457
00:20:39,333 --> 00:20:41,166
Come back!

458
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:42,208
[DOG barks]

459
00:20:43,583 --> 00:20:46,208
Yeah. That Classic Lit
test was a total disaster.

460
00:20:46,291 --> 00:20:48,458
[STUDENT 4H] I'll say,
it was a difficult one indeed.

461
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,291
[KIMITO]
So tell me...

462
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:53,333
Are you two using
your cellphones?

463
00:20:53,416 --> 00:20:54,791
Yes. Sometimes.

464
00:20:54,875 --> 00:20:56,083
Not often though,

465
00:20:56,166 --> 00:20:57,541
because we see each other
every day at school.

466
00:20:57,625 --> 00:20:59,666
In reality,
there isn't much need.

467
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:01,083
True.

468
00:21:01,166 --> 00:21:03,291
So you don't even send
each other messages in class?

469
00:21:03,375 --> 00:21:04,625
[STUDENT 4H]
Oh, good gracious no.

470
00:21:04,708 --> 00:21:06,125
We have to conceal
our phones at school

471
00:21:06,208 --> 00:21:07,791
for fear of being reprimanded.

472
00:21:07,875 --> 00:21:09,208
[STUDENT 6Q] We text
quite a bit in our rooms

473
00:21:09,291 --> 00:21:11,125
before bedtime, though.

474
00:21:11,208 --> 00:21:12,250
What about you?

475
00:21:12,333 --> 00:21:13,291
Huh?

476
00:21:15,375 --> 00:21:17,583
Obviously, I don't
have anyone to text.

477
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:19,333
In that case,
you should text with me!

478
00:21:19,416 --> 00:21:20,458
Yes! For sure.

479
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:22,541
The three of us
should group text!

480
00:21:22,625 --> 00:21:23,833
We should?

481
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:31,708
[AIKA]
Sure!

482
00:21:31,791 --> 00:21:34,750
--[STUDENTS chattering]
--[AIKA laughing]

483
00:21:39,791 --> 00:21:42,041
[STUDENT 6V] Would it be all
right if I texted you, too?

484
00:21:42,125 --> 00:21:43,250
[AIKA]
Of course!

485
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:45,291
[laughter continues]

486
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:55,958
[SAKIMORI]
What are you doing, Hakua?

487
00:21:56,041 --> 00:21:57,750
Are you all right?

488
00:23:32,708 --> 00:23:33,875
Don't get too cocky.

489
00:23:33,958 --> 00:23:36,208
[KAREN gasps]
It's the ultimate humiliation!

490
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:40,000
Kimito's lips are soft,
and feel really great!

491
00:23:40,083 --> 00:23:41,041
[REIKO]
Yes, it is better.

492
00:23:41,125 --> 00:23:43,041
I despise you, Kimito!

493
00:23:43,125 --> 00:23:44,541
Guess this is the end
of the Commoner Club.

494
00:23:44,625 --> 00:23:46,791
It sure is fun
having lots of friends!

